modules.description: Provides functions to establish and manage audio connections, control port registration, and handle audio processing callbacks within the JACK framework. Works with audio ports, client contexts, and sample data represented as arrays. Used to create real-time audio applications that route signals between software components in a low-latency environment.

This module offers low-level control over audio devices via a handle, enabling operations like buffer management, volume adjustment, and playback state manipulation within the JACK audio system. It interacts with JACK client state objects to retrieve metrics such as sample rates, channel counts, and buffer statistics, facilitating real-time audio configuration and monitoring. Use cases include precise audio latency tuning, dynamic volume control, and diagnostic analysis of audio client performance.
